<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-512-967  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 512 967.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Oct 15 1990 n488 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ameritech inks $2M deal. (Ameritech Information Systems contractwith Roberts Express Inc)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Medford, Cassimir.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ameritech Information Systems wins Roberts Express Inc's $2million, 18-month contract to build a distributed database for thecenterpiece of Roberts' communications network.andP;  Roberts, asurface carrier that specializes in door-to-door transportation oftime-sensitive shipments and shipments requiring special handling,rejected bids from ATandamp;T and Wang Laboratories.andP;  Roberts uses 1,200agent-owned trucks equipped with communications links that areconnected to the company's 200-terminal network.andP;  Unlike itscompetitors, Ameritech's solution, which is is based on IngresCorp's fourth-generation on-line transaction processing database,offered Roberts low risk, a guaranteed price and support services.andO;The distributed database system will manage a wide range ofRoberts' business information from real-time data on trucklocation to payroll.andP;  The system will be operational Jan 1991.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Ameritech Publishing Inc. Ameritech Information Systems(contracts)Roberts Express Inc. (contracts).andO;Topic:     Distributed Data BasesCommunications ApplicationsTransportationCompetitionComputer Systems IntegrationOn-Line Transaction ProcessingMarketing Strategy.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Ameritech's database project. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>